---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
const updated = '30 June 2026';
---
<Legal
  title="Terms of Use | CyberCap"
  description="The terms governing use of the CyberCap website."
  heading="Terms of Use"
  updated={updated}
>
  <p>These terms govern your use of the <strong>{site.name}</strong> website. By using this site, you agree to them.</p>

  <h2>1. Information only</h2>
  <p>
    The content on this website is provided for general information about our services. It does not constitute
    professional, legal or security advice, and no client relationship is created by using the site. Engagements
    are governed by a separate written agreement.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>All content, branding and materials on this site are owned by {site.name} or its licensors and may not be reproduced without permission.</p>

  <h2>3. No warranties</h2>
  <p>The site is provided "as is". We make reasonable efforts to keep it accurate and available but do not guarantee it will be error-free or uninterrupted.</p>

  <h2>4. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>To the extent permitted by law, {site.name} is not liable for any loss arising from use of, or reliance on, this website.</p>

  <h2>5. External links</h2>
  <p>We are not responsible for the content of third-party websites linked from this site.</p>

  <h2>6. Governing law</h2>
  <p>These terms are governed by Belgian law, and any disputes are subject to the competent courts of [your jurisdiction].</p>

  <h2>7. Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about these terms? Email us at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>

  <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-slate"><em>This document is a template provided to help you launch. Please have it reviewed before relying on it.</em></p>
</Legal>
